definition: Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono (1949-), retired Indonesian general, president of the Republic of Indonesia 2004-2014
Perilla frutescens (Chinese basil or wild red basil)/place name/to revive/used as phonetic in transliteration
surname Su/abbr. for Soviet Union 蘇維埃|苏维埃 or 蘇聯|苏联/abbr. for Jiangsu province 江蘇|江苏/abbr. for Suzhou city 蘇州|苏州
the West/abbr. for Spain 西班牙[Xi1 ban1 ya2]/Spanish
surname Luo/old name of several rivers (in Henan, Shaanxi, Sichuan and Anhui)

sentences.english: Susilo also indicated that Indonesia resolutely pursues the one-China policy.
sentences.chinese: 蘇西洛還表示，印尼堅定奉行一箇中國政策。

sentences.english: Wen conveyed President Hu Jintao’s cordial greetings to Susilo.
sentences.chinese: 溫家寶向蘇西洛轉達了胡錦濤主席的親切問候。

sentences.english: The President will attend a series of events in central Java.
sentences.chinese: 據悉，總統蘇西洛將會參加爪哇島中部的一系列活動。
